        {
          "name": "leafIndex",
          "ty_idx": 9
        },
        {
          "name": "mergeProof",
          "ty_idx": 15
        }
      ],
      "description": "Deposit native TON into the pool.\n\nThe depositor proves on-chain that `newRoot` is the result of inserting\n`commitment` at `leafIndex` into the tree with root `prevRoot`. The\npool checks `prevRoot == storage.currentRoot` and\n`leafIndex == storage.nextIndex`, so the only path through the deposit\nhandler is \"extend the canonical tree by exactly one paid commitment.\"\nA single paid deposit cannot register a multi-leaf attacker tree."
    },
